message.content: An 'Argia tibialis' is a species of damselfly, commonly found in North America. It has a long, slender body and wings that are held flat when at rest. The male has a blue-green thorax and abdomen, while the female has a brownish-green coloring. The wings are transparent with black veins and a distinct black pterostigma. The eyes are large and prominent with a metallic green coloration. 'Argia tibialis' can be found near slow-moving bodies of water such as streams, ponds, and lakes, and are often seen resting on vegetation near these areas. Overall, they are a beautiful and distinctive species of damselfly to observe in their natural habitat.
